** Need root user access or a sudoers user. 

 

 

STEP 1 

Install JDK 11 using below command 
sudo yum install java-11-openjdk-devel 
 

STEP 2 

Install Kafka and Zookeeper using below commands. 
Download Kafka using below command 
wget https://downloads.apache.org/kafka/3.0.2/kafka_2.12-3.0.2.tgz -O /opt/kafka_2.12-3.0.2.tgz 
Unzip the file into /opt directory 
cd /opt 
tar -xvf kafka_2.12-3.0.2.tgz 
Create symbolic link to the Kafka home directory 
ln -s /opt/kafka_2.12-3.0.2.tgz /opt/kafka 
Add a user to run both Kafka & Zookeeper 
useradd kafka 
Grant the ownership to Kafka user to the entire home directory 
chown -R kafka:kafka /opt/kafka* 
Create an unit file inside /etc/systemd/system/zookeeper.service for Zookeeper service 
[Unit] 
Description=zookeeper 
After=syslog.target network.target 
[Service] 
Type=simple 
User=kafka 
Group=kafka 
ExecStart=/opt/kafka/bin/zookeeper-server-start.sh /opt/kafka/config/zookeeper.properties 
ExecStop=/opt/kafka/bin/zookeeper-server-stop.sh 
[Install] 
WantedBy=multi-user.target 
Create an unit file inside /etc/systemd/system/kafka.service for Kafka service 
[Unit] 
Description=Apache Kafka 
Requires=zookeeper.service 
After=zookeeper.service 
[Service] 
Type=simple 
User=kafka 
Group=kafka 

ExecStart=/opt/kafka/bin/kafka-server-start.sh /opt/kafka/config/server.properties 
ExecStop=/opt/kafka/bin/kafka-server-stop.sh 

[Install] 

WantedBy=multi-user.target 

Reload the systemd to read new unit files 

systemctl daemon-reload 

Start the new services using below commands 

systemctl start zookeeper 

 

 

systemctl start kafka 

Enable the new services in-order to start them at OS reboot. 

systemctl enable zookeeper.service 

 

 

systemctl enable kafka.service 

 

 

